         <abstract>
            <p>Let $\theta$ denote the positive root of the equation $x^3 + x^2 - 2x - 1 = 0$; that is, $\theta = 2 \cos(2\pi/7)$. The main result of the paper is the evaluation of the constant $\lim \sup_{M \rightarrow \infty} \min M^2|x + \theta y + \theta^2 z|$, where the $\min$ is taken over all integers $x, y, z$ satisfying $1 \leqq \max (|y|, |z|) \leqq M$. Its value is $(2\theta + 3)/7 \approx .78485$. The same method can be applied to other constants of the same type.</p>
          </abstract>
